data.name: realismCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Enables Armour and Ammo changes, the core of Realism Mod. Player and bot health will also no longer be adjusted and starting profiles no longer changed. If disabled, current armour durablity and player health will not be corrected but max durability/health will be.

data.name: masteryCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Changes what weapons fall into what Mastery categories. Weapons that have similar controls or reload operation are in the same category. For most weapons, mastery will come a lot quicker because of this.

data.name: recoilAttOverhaulCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Enables the complete overhaul of recoil and attachments. See the mod's overview page on the hub for details. IF YOU WANT TO DISABLE THIS FEATURE YOU MUST DELETE THE REALISMMOD.DLL FROM YOUR BEPINEX/PLUGINS FOLDER. OTHERWISE YOUR GAME WILL CRASH!

data.name: buffHelmetsCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Buffs helmets and faceshields by raising their armor level by 1. Their blunt throughput has been modified to compensate. Not carefully balanced, just for those that want a slightly less hardcore experience.

data.name: medChangesCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Enables changes to medical items to be more hardcore. Only stims, surgery kits and new craftable makeshift medical kits will restore HP. Most meds now have debuffs to simulate the wound trauma from getting shot and the negative effects of tourniquets on the body. See the mod overview page for details.

data.name: botDiffGroupBox.ToolTip
data.value: PMC and Boss difficulty will be raised, if set to true. Only use if not using FAIL or other AI mods. Will just simply set bosses and PMC from 'AsOnline' to a higher difficulty settings (Hard or Impossible). Not compatible with FAIL, use that instead if you need to choose one or the other.

data.name: botHealthGroupBox.ToolTip
data.value: Bot health settings. If set to true, these bot types will have the same health as the player. If false, they will have default EFT health pools. Realism option must be true for this to take effect. If realism is false, all bots will have defualt health.

data.name: tieredFleaCheck.ToolTip
data.value: If Enabled the fleamarket will unlock progressivly by category or subcategory of item based on the player's level. There are 7 tiers in total, the final one being a 'full unlock'. Most items are no longer blacklisted from the flea.

data.name: traderChangesCheck.ToolTip
data.value: Enables changes to trader sell categories to be more unique and make more sense. For now just changes what Therapist, Skier and Mechanic will buy, Fence's inventory and cost of Therapist's healing. Many more changes to traders will come in the future.

data.name: airdropChangesCheck.ToolTip
data.value: If enabled airdrops will have 'types' (medical supplies, food, ammo, etc.) and will only have items of that type. Different types have different rarity, airdrop types will be rerolled when starting the game or at the end of raids.

data.name: devToolsTextBox.Text
data.value: Testing parameters. For testing purposes only. No support given if these are enabled. First enable bot testing. Set the tier to 1-4 to spawn a sepcific tier of bot, then set what what bot type you want to spawn. Disabling weapons will deactivate the AI, they will spawn but not move or react.
